The police in KwaZulu-Natal have closed the R74 road near Langkloof outside Bergville following a motor vehicle accident involving two vehicles. It is reported that six people have died, while five other people sustained injuries. #sapsKZN Police have closed the R74 near Langkloof area outside Bergville following a motor vehicle accident involving two vehicles. Six fatalities, 5 injured. Culpable homicide case opened. Traffic is being diverted. ME pic.twitter.com/TsnJuT2Dvn — SA Police Service (@SAPoliceService) March 6, 2018 A case of culpable homicide case has been opened. More to follow as the story develops